'''Value trumping''' is the "precedence of certain [[cultural values]] over others" in certain contexts,<ref>Osland, Joyce S., and Allan Bird. "Beyond sophisticated stereotyping: Cultural sensemaking in context." The Academy of Management Executive 14.1 (2000): 65-77.</ref> whereas the same value may not be trumping other values under different circumstances.<ref name="BoyacigillerGoodman2004">{{cite book|author1=Nakiye Avdan Boyacigiller|author2=Richard Alan Goodman|author3=Margaret E. Phillips|title=Crossing Cultures: Insights from Master Teachers|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DAl_AgAAQBAJ&pg=PA92|date=2 August 2004|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-134-39581-1|pages=92}}</ref> The term is usually applied to cultural or group values, where the members adapt to specific circumstances.<ref>Clausen, Lisbeth. "Moving beyond stereotypes in managing cultural difference: Communication in Danish–Japanese corporate relationships." Scandinavian Journal of Management 26.1 (2010): 57-66.</ref><ref>Bell, Roger. "Paradoxes of culture: how to make more accurate interpretations." Handbook of Business Strategy 7.1 (2006): 363-368.</ref>

